            <p>Mark Milner has served as interim and is now the Chief Nursing Officer   at Ephraim McDowell Regional Medical Center since August, 2015. Prior to   taking that role, he was Vice President of Clinical Effectiveness for   Ephraim McDowell Health starting in 2014. Before coming to Kentucky,   Mark was the System Director of Outcomes Management at NCH in Naples,   Florida. Previous to that position, his professional and clinical   background include Assistant Vice President for Oschner Health Systems,   System Director for Baptist Health, Vice President with Health First   Health System, Director with The Joint Commission, and Vice President   with the Florida Hospital Association. Mark is an RN with an MHS, MBA,   BFA, and BS. He is completing his BSN in November. He has been a board   member of KAHQ, FAHQ, and LAHQ. Using the Baldridge criteria, he has   performed surveys for the Kentucky Center for Performance Excellence,   and the Florida Governor&rsquo;s Sterling Award programs. He was a member of   the adjunct, graduate-school faculty at Tulane, and Webster   Universities. In addition, his certifications include CPHQ, ACM, and   FACHE. Mark is a highly skilled and experienced professional nurse   leader who continues to successfully demonstrate building best practice   platforms that promote and support nursing excellence.</p><hr>

