            <p>Mr. Carr is the vice president of clinical services for Alliant   Management Services. In this role, Mr. Carr is responsible for providing   clinical consultative services to the managed hospitals as well as to   select clients in other hospitals. He provides additional services   related to productivity program establishment, improvement, and   management, clinical performance improvement, accreditation/licensure   preparedness, staff development, clinical education, clinical   benchmarking, and new clinical service development. Prior to assuming   his current position, Mr. Carr was the director for clinical services   for another major hospital management company, providing much of the   same services for over 200 hospitals nationwide that he now provides for   Alliant Management Services. And, before that, he was vice president of   patient services of a hospital where he served 23 years. He has added   experience in infection control, performance improvement, cost   containment, and a variety of other clinical initiatives. Mr. Carr has   over 40 years of experience in health care. Mr. Carr has served on the   Kentucky Board of Nursing as a representative for the Kentucky   Organization of Nurse Executives (now KONL); served previously as Ohio   Valley District Representative for the Kentucky Organization of Nurse   Leaders; and has held numerous offices in nursing and other healthcare   organizations. Mr. Carr is a Nurse Executive Advanced, Board Certified   and is a Certified Joint Commission Professional.</p><hr>

