            <p>Lynne Warner Lynn, MSN, RN, NE-BC, FCN is director of Nursing   Administration at Ephraim McDowell Regional Medical Center (EMRMC) and   system director of Regulatory Compliance, Associate Education and   Community Services for Ephraim McDowell Health. Lynn is responsible for   administering nursing in the absence of the organization&rsquo;s nurse   executive/CNO. She directs and coordinates The Joint Commission   accreditation (TJC) process for the system and works with a variety of   disciplines and levels of staff across departments and the health system   related to accreditation readiness. She coordinates hospital wide and   nursing specific licensure surveys and complaint investigations and   provides leadership and supervision to EMRMC to ensure that quality   services are provided by a sufficient number of qualified and competent   staff. She consults and collaborates with interdisciplinary teams to   facilitate quality patient care, appropriate bed placement, assess   education needs, provide community services through a variety of means,   and evaluate performance improvement initiates for specific populations.</p>
            <p>Lynn, a clinical nurse specialist, has 32 years of nursing experience   as a registered nurse and over two-thirds of that time spent in   healthcare leadership. She has served as adjunct faculty at community   and technical facilities and has a wide-range of nursing experience in   various settings including community hospitals, regional medical   centers, faith-based organizations, trauma and academic centers, and   home health agencies. She holds a Master of Science in nursing degree   from the University of Kentucky, a certification as a nurse executive   from the ANCC and is a certified faith community nurse. She chairs and   serves on several committees/councils within EMH in addition to serving   as chair of the Membership committee of the Kentucky Organization of   Nurse Leaders (KONL), a member of the Bluegrass Technical and Community   Colleges (BCTC) Nursing Division Advisory Board, Kentucky Hospital   Association Accreditation committee, Hope Clinic Advisory board, Sigma   Theta Tau International Honor Society of Nursing, Golden Key Honorary   Society, and other community and church positions.</p>
